In reproductive therapy, the quality of experience of involuntarily childless women and their partners takes second place. In the following article, the experiences in various areas of life (partnership, family, profession, friends and acquaintances) are described from the subjective view of the persons affected. Issues are the peculiarities of the female position in life and the reproductive function. Conflicts in different areas of life are described from the point of view of the persons affected. The diverse aspects of the unfulfilled wish for a child become clear and, above all, the emotional isolation of the persons affected. The permanent feeling of failure and insufficiency emerges.  
